1
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:43,039
You saw the eye pattern on the silver eye

2
00:00:43,240 --> 00:00:44,280
and nearly passed out

3
00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:47,280
because you have an eye-shaped scar too

4
00:00:49,719 --> 00:00:51,039
When did you find out?

5
00:00:51,280 --> 00:00:52,560
I found out before we set out

6
00:00:53,359 --> 00:00:54,799
My scar

7
00:00:55,759 --> 00:00:56,840
is different from yours

8
00:00:57,520 --> 00:00:59,399
I've had my scar

9
00:00:59,399 --> 00:01:00,359
since I was born

10
00:01:00,359 --> 00:01:01,880
For most of my life

11
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:05,200
I've been investigating this

12
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:06,480
I never expected

13
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:10,079
to find it's connected to the Lingxiao Pearl

14
00:01:11,519 --> 00:01:13,120
You want to find the Lingxiao Pearl

15
00:01:14,359 --> 00:01:15,519
to cure yourself

16
00:01:18,439 --> 00:01:19,680
I gave up that naive notion

17
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:21,519
twenty years ago

18
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:23,560
Now

19
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:28,000
I just want to know what secret

20
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,400
the Lingxiao Pearl truly holds

21
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:32,680
Then my life won't have been in vain

22
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:36,159
Brother Chen

23
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:38,879
Out of everyone

24
00:01:39,239 --> 00:01:42,640
I, Lian Ximin, trust only you

25
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:45,640
All I seek in this life

26
00:01:45,879 --> 00:01:47,480
is to know what secret

27
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:49,280
lies hidden in the Lingxiao Pearl

28
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:50,560
Believe me

29
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:53,840
I'll never keep it for myself

30
00:02:01,439 --> 00:02:02,159
Let's go

31
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:03,760
Go on

32
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:04,920
Take care of those wounds

33
00:02:05,519 --> 00:02:06,840
Don't get hurt next time

34
00:02:07,439 --> 00:02:10,000
You'll never change, will you?

35
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:11,400
Let's go, come on

36
00:02:14,199 --> 00:02:15,400
Old Chen, Fatty

37
00:02:15,719 --> 00:02:16,759
We'll drink when you're back!

38
00:02:39,039 --> 00:02:40,199
Brother Lu, are you okay?

39
00:02:40,199 --> 00:02:41,120
How could I be okay?

40
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,240
Need a spray?

41
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:42,919
Spray it, spray it

42
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,639
The altitude here is only 2,000-something

43
00:02:47,919 --> 00:02:49,439
and you're reacting this badly

44
00:02:49,439 --> 00:02:50,840
What'll you do when we go higher?

45
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:52,000
N-Nonsense

46
00:02:52,479 --> 00:02:53,280
My head hurts

47
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:54,960
Want another spray then?

48
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:57,280
Ignore him. Let him pass out.

49
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:47,280
He hit someone! He hit someone!

50
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,120
Where are you hurt?

51
00:03:48,439 --> 00:03:49,560
Where does it hurt? You okay?

52
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:51,599
Should we go to the hospital? It hurts so bad!

53
00:03:51,719 --> 00:03:53,280
My leg hurts! My leg!

54
00:03:56,479 --> 00:03:58,280
You can't leave, you can't go

55
00:03:58,560 --> 00:03:59,599
You can't leave

56
00:03:59,719 --> 00:04:00,520
What are you doing?

57
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,080
He hit someone!

58
00:04:02,319 --> 00:04:03,000
Let go!

59
00:04:04,319 --> 00:04:05,879
You can't go, you can't leave

60
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:19,439
You okay?

61
00:04:19,439 --> 00:04:20,000
Get out of the way

62
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:39,959
The cops are here! Cops!

63
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:01,560
Stop fighting! Stop! Stop!

64
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,279
Stop fighting!

65
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:06,319
Xiao Qi.

66
00:05:13,399 --> 00:05:14,360
Have something to eat.

67
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,399
Thanks.

68
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,600
Help yourself.

69
00:05:19,279 --> 00:05:20,079
Have some snacks.

70
00:05:20,079 --> 00:05:20,879
Thanks.

71
00:05:27,639 --> 00:05:30,399
Commander Chen, so this is Xiao Qi?

72
00:05:30,519 --> 00:05:31,839
Look at those pearly whites.

73
00:05:31,839 --> 00:05:32,600
No mistake about it.

74
00:05:32,959 --> 00:05:36,519
Brother Chen, this man here is Dawang.

75
00:05:36,519 --> 00:05:38,680
He's the one taking us to Xiaduo Yuzhang.

76
00:05:41,079 --> 00:05:43,720
I just heard you want to go to Xiaduo Yuzhang.

77
00:05:44,399 --> 00:05:45,480
So, Brother Xiao Qi,

78
00:05:45,839 --> 00:05:46,959
I'd like to ask you,

79
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:49,079
what exactly is Xiaduo Yuzhang?

80
00:05:49,319 --> 00:05:51,800
Why does everyone we meet on the road

81
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:53,399
react like they've seen a ghost when they hear it?

82
00:05:53,439 --> 00:05:54,920
Did the place do something to you guys?

83
00:05:56,079 --> 00:05:57,879
There's nothing special about the place itself.

84
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:00,079
But in our ancient legends,

85
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,680
it symbolizes a sea of disaster.

86
00:06:05,399 --> 00:06:06,600
It's a place of ill omen.

87
00:06:08,319 --> 00:06:09,120
Brother Xiao Qi,

88
00:06:09,279 --> 00:06:10,120
I still have to trouble you

89
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,680
to please guide us into the mountains.

90
00:06:19,079 --> 00:06:19,879
I'm counting on you.

91
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:27,839
I'm exhausted.

92
00:06:29,439 --> 00:06:30,879
What's all this ginger juice for?

93
00:06:30,879 --> 00:06:32,120
You planning to brew ginger soup up there?

94
00:06:32,120 --> 00:06:32,920
If you're afraid of the cold,

95
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:35,120
wouldn't a couple bottles of liquor be better?

96
00:06:35,639 --> 00:06:38,240
Looks like you really did come prepared.

97
00:06:39,199 --> 00:06:40,920
Hey, hauling a barrel of ginger juice,

98
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:42,839
how does that count as being prepared?

99
00:06:43,160 --> 00:06:44,759
The glaciers up on the Kunlun Mountains

100
00:06:44,959 --> 00:06:46,560
are ancient ice, millions of years old.

101
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:48,680
You can't imagine how solid they are.

102
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:50,879
Even swinging a pickaxe is useless.

103
00:06:50,879 --> 00:06:51,800
Ordinary tools

104
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,360
basically can't cut through that ice.

105
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:56,040
Old Chen,

106
00:06:56,439 --> 00:06:59,600
you had us gather ginger juice to melt the ice?

107
00:06:59,639 --> 00:07:01,240
Brother Xiao Qi already said it.

108
00:07:01,319 --> 00:07:04,040
The Nine-Tier Pagoda is beneath that ancient glacier.

109
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:05,480
We don't know how deep it goes.

110
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:06,560
Better safe than sorry.

111
00:07:17,519 --> 00:07:18,759
Those are black-necked water birds.

112
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:20,480
What about them?

113
00:07:20,959 --> 00:07:22,600
They're coming from the north.

114
00:07:24,839 --> 00:07:26,040
Black-necked water birds normally

115
00:07:26,040 --> 00:07:27,199
don't get startled easily.

116
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:29,800
Even if an avalanche hit the northern mountains,

117
00:07:30,279 --> 00:07:31,600
you'd rarely see them fly off.

118
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:35,040
The mountain pass we're heading to,

119
00:07:35,759 --> 00:07:36,680
it's to the north.

120
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,279
That's right.

121
00:07:39,279 --> 00:07:40,879
From here to the Xiaduo Yuzhang pass,

122
00:07:40,879 --> 00:07:42,399
it'll take at least four days.

123
00:07:43,079 --> 00:07:44,519
We'd better set off as soon as possible.

124
00:08:10,319 --> 00:08:11,120
Be careful!

125
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:28,399
What a deep gorge.

126
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:34,360
Elder Chen.

127
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:52,679
Brother Chen.

128
00:08:53,519 --> 00:08:54,399
What are you thinking about?

129
00:08:55,519 --> 00:08:56,320
Scared stiff?

130
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:58,840
This must be the Valley of Dry Bones.

131
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:00,639
I hadn't said a word,

132
00:09:00,639 --> 00:09:01,759
and you already figured it out.

133
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:03,200
I originally thought the Valley of Dry Bones

134
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:03,840
was just an ordinary path

135
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:05,679
on the way to Xiaduo Yuzhang.

136
00:09:06,159 --> 00:09:07,360
I didn't expect that this time,

137
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:08,559
we'd have to take it.

138
00:09:09,879 --> 00:09:11,120
What do you mean?

139
00:09:11,559 --> 00:09:13,200
Ancient sites of this kind

140
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:14,879
always come with two equally-sized

141
00:09:14,879 --> 00:09:16,360
dragon-shaped burial trenches alongside.

142
00:09:17,919 --> 00:09:19,960
You suspect this Valley of Dry Bones

143
00:09:20,159 --> 00:09:22,200
could be one of the burial trenches

144
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,639
near the Nine-Tier Pagoda?

145
00:09:23,919 --> 00:09:26,600
Yes, I'm guessing this is one of them.

146
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:29,200
Inside this Valley of Dry Bones, we'll surely find

147
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,200
more information about the Nine-Tier Pagoda.

148
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:26,000
An Xiang, take a look at this place.

149
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:27,480
What do you think?

150
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:21,600
See anything?

151
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,039
That's good then.

152
00:11:25,519 --> 00:11:28,200
The old folks used to say

153
00:11:28,919 --> 00:11:30,320
that for hundreds of years,

154
00:11:30,480 --> 00:11:32,080
every year, huge numbers

155
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:34,720
of gazelles, bison, and wild horses would jump to their deaths.

156
00:11:37,639 --> 00:11:38,879
The phenomenon of wild animals

157
00:11:39,279 --> 00:11:41,720
committing suicide in herds

158
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:42,879
happens all over the world.

159
00:11:43,279 --> 00:11:44,759
But I've never heard of

160
00:11:44,759 --> 00:11:45,960
different species of animals

161
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:47,399
all killing themselves together.

162
00:11:47,399 --> 00:11:48,759
This is what the elders say.

163
00:11:48,919 --> 00:11:50,480
In ancient legends,

164
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:52,000
whenever there's a full moon,

165
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,759
the beasts would gaze up at the moon

166
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:55,120
and then leap down,

167
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:56,840
to appease the wrath of the heavens.

168
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:07,159
It's fine.

169
00:12:31,679 --> 00:12:32,480
It's solid.

170
00:12:32,919 --> 00:12:34,519
Look, look, he just walked right across!

171
00:12:39,799 --> 00:12:40,480
Get back, get back!

172
00:12:41,799 --> 00:12:42,840
You, come back, come back!

173
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:43,679
Get back here!

174
00:12:46,639 --> 00:12:47,879
It's hollow underneath.

175
00:12:48,799 --> 00:12:49,600
Hollow?

176
00:12:52,559 --> 00:12:53,679
It really is hollow.

177
00:12:54,919 --> 00:12:55,919
Not entirely.

178
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:58,120
Otherwise, how would these bones pile up?

179
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:01,399
These animal bones interlock like fangs,

180
00:13:01,679 --> 00:13:02,559
hooking together easily.

181
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:05,679
That's what creates this illusion of solid ground.

182
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:09,000
These canines and carnassials are so developed,

183
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:11,039
and the upper molars have distinct cusps.

184
00:13:12,759 --> 00:13:14,120
It couldn't be a tiger, could it?

185
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:14,840
Wild dogs?

186
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:15,799
They're wolves.

187
00:13:16,519 --> 00:13:17,200
Wolves?

188
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,559
If that's the case,

189
00:13:21,879 --> 00:13:22,960
then these fresh bones

190
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:24,960
are all leftovers from wolf hunts.

191
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:28,679
Let's go catch ourselves a wolf,

192
00:13:28,919 --> 00:13:29,919
tie a rope around it,

193
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:32,080
put it in front, let it walk first,

194
00:13:32,159 --> 00:13:34,279
then we follow in its footprints.

195
00:13:34,639 --> 00:13:35,799
That way we won't fall through.

196
00:13:35,799 --> 00:13:36,279
What do you mean?

197
00:13:36,279 --> 00:13:39,000
Catch a wolf to lead the way? Seriously?

198
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,720
Are you kidding me?

199
00:13:40,799 --> 00:13:43,200
Brother Chen, what should we actually do?

200
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,840
Wolves are clever and cunning.

201
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:57,240
They've hunted here for years,

202
00:13:57,440 --> 00:13:59,240
so they must know this terrain

203
00:13:59,399 --> 00:14:00,519
like the back of their hand.

204
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:03,200
With all their long-term trial and error,

205
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:05,679
where they step is the safest ground.

206
00:14:05,879 --> 00:14:07,200
What we need to do now

207
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:08,759
is examine the shape of these bones,

208
00:14:08,759 --> 00:14:10,039
to see if they've been gnawed on.

209
00:14:10,039 --> 00:14:11,440
If they've been chewed,

210
00:14:11,759 --> 00:14:13,120
then that's where the wolves stepped.

211
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:14,279
Got it.

212
00:14:14,519 --> 00:14:15,399
You mean,

213
00:14:16,039 --> 00:14:19,000
we follow the path the wolves took,

214
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,279
and we'll be safe?

215
00:14:21,039 --> 00:14:21,840
Yes.

216
00:14:30,519 --> 00:14:31,039
Come on.

217
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:36,440
Let me help you.

218
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:37,240
I don't need help.

219
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:38,440
I need to take a leak.

220
00:14:39,039 --> 00:14:40,000
Go on then, fine, fine.

221
00:14:40,399 --> 00:14:41,279
Hurry up!

222
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:42,879
Don't fall too far behind!

223
00:14:48,159 --> 00:14:49,399
I'm exhausted.

224
00:14:50,919 --> 00:14:52,360
An Xiang's a good kid.

225
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:54,600
Pretty down-to-earth.

226
00:14:57,720 --> 00:14:59,279
Help!

227
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:01,039
Old Lu! Old Lu!

228
00:15:02,879 --> 00:15:03,559
Old Lu!

229
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:05,039
Old Lu!

